":300,"TotalIntervalTimeoutForAsyncInSeconds":3600,"Parameters":[{"CustomActionId":0,"IsMandatory":true,"DefaultValue":"","Description":"Specify a comma-separated list of IDs or UUIDs of the events for which you want retrieve details.","Name":"Event ID","Value":"","Type":0,"OptionalValues":null,"OptionalValuesJson":null},{"CustomActionId":0,"IsMandatory":false,"DefaultValue":"True","Description":"If enabled, action will create a case wall table for all of the attributes that are a part of the event.","Name":"Return Attributes Info","Value":"True","Type":1,"OptionalValues":null,"OptionalValuesJson":null}],"DefaultResultValue":null,"PythonVersion":"None","ActionType":1,"SimulationData":{"Entities":null},"SimulationDataJson":null,"AICategories":[],"OutcomeCategories":[],"AIDescription":"### General Description\\nThe **Get Event Details** action retrieves comprehensive information about specific events from a MISP instance using their unique identifiers (IDs or UUIDs). This action is useful for analysts who need to deep-dive into known MISP events to understand the associated attributes, threat levels, and organizational context.\\n\\n### Parameters Description\\n| Parameter | Type | Mandatory | Description |\\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\\n| **Event ID** | String | Yes | A comma-separated list of MISP Event IDs or UUIDs to retrieve. |\\n| **Return Attributes Info** | Boolean | No | If enabled (default), the action will generate an additional data table containing details for all attributes associated with the event. |\\n\\n### Flow Description\\n1. **Parameter Extraction**: The action parses the provided comma-separated list of Event IDs and the boolean flag for attribute retrieval.\\n2. **API Interaction**: For each Event ID, the action queries the MISP API to fetch the full event object.\\n3. **Data Processing**: The raw event data is captured for the action's JSON output.\\n4. **Case Wall Updates**:\\n    * A data table named 'Event {ID} Details' is created, showing flattened event metadata (e.g., Org, Date, Threat Level).\\n    * If 'Return Attributes Info' is true, a second table named 'Event {ID} Attributes Details' is created, listing all attributes (e.g., type, value, category) linked to that event.\\n5. **Final Reporting**: The action concludes by summarizing which events were successfully retrieved and which failed.","AiShortDescription":null,"ParametersDescription":null,"EntityTypes":[]}